sustainability of continued software maintenance. Individuals, academics,
hobbyists, and non-commercial open source projects receive perpetual,
royalty-free access. Commercial entities that derive economic value from
the Work are required to contribute to its ongoing development through
reasonable licensing fees. This ensures the Work remains free for those
who cannot pay while allowing those who benefit commercially to support
the project. The terms below define the precise boundaries of these rights
and obligations.

