Recipient's current revenue tier. The certificate shall be signed by an
authorized executive officer of the Recipient, which shall be the Chief
Executive Officer, Chief Financial Officer, or General Counsel.

4.2 Audit Rights. Licensor may trigger an independent certified public
accountant audit of Recipient's compliance with this Covenant upon: (a)
reasonable suspicion generated by public engineering logs, job descriptions,
telemetry metrics, or other publicly available information; or (b) an automatic
random audit protocol applicable to any Commercial Entity whose annual revenue
exceeds ten million United States dollars ($10,000,000 USD). Audits shall be
limited to once per calendar year and may be conducted only upon thirty (30)
days' written notice to Recipient. If an audit reveals underreporting of
license fees by more than five percent (5%), Recipient shall bear the
reasonable costs of the audit. Recipient may redact proprietary, privileged,
or personal data protected by applicable data protection laws, but must
provide sufficient information to verify compliance.

4.3 Personal Liability of Signing Officers. The executive officer who executes
the compliance certification under Section 4.1 on behalf of a Commercial Entity
does not assume personal liability for the Commercial Entity's compliance with
this Covenant in the ordinary course of business. Personal liability shall
attach to such officer in their individual capacity only if Licensor proves
by clear and convincing evidence that: (a) the certification was false in a
material respect; (b) the officer had actual knowledge of such material
falsity at the time of signing; (c) the officer acted with specific intent
to defraud Licensor; and (d) such fraud constituted willful corporate
concealment, including but not limited to deliberately hiding commercial
usage of the Work for a period of two (2) or more years.

4.4 Liability Caps for Small Violators. Notwithstanding any other provision
of this Covenant, total damages recoverable from a Recipient for violation
of this Covenant shall be capped at ten thousand United States dollars
($10,000 USD) for entities with annual revenue under five hundred thousand
United States dollars ($500,000 USD), and at five hundred United States dollars
($500 USD) for individuals with annual revenue under ten thousand United States
dollars ($10,000 USD).

4.5 Termination for Non-Compliance. If a Recipient fails to cure any breach
of this Covenant within thirty (30) days of receiving written notice thereof
from Licensor, this Covenant and all rights granted hereunder shall terminate.
Upon termination, Recipient shall immediately cease all use of the Work and
